R3 fingerprint: `<!-- agent-fp: 984201e58b86 -->`.

## Trigger scenario

1. A user outside Saudi Arabia (or inside KSA but without a KSA billing address and no CF-IPCountry header) initiates a subscription checkout with `provider: "tabby"` via `POST /api/v1/commerce/subscriptions/checkout`.
2. The route parses the body with `SubscriptionCheckoutSchema`, which accepts `provider: z.enum(PAYMENT_PROVIDERS)` — Tabby is in `PAYMENT_PROVIDERS`.
3. No Tabby eligibility check is performed. The command is passed directly to `handleSubscriptionCheckout()`.
4. `handleSubscriptionCheckout()` calls the Tabby payment gateway. Tabby rejects the request server-side (the gateway itself enforces KSA-only).
5. The route returns a **502 gateway error** (or a generic 500) with `{error: "Failed to create checkout session"}`.
6. The client-side error handler in `use-course-detail.ts` checks `data.code === "TABBY_KSA_ONLY"` to show the localized billing-address prompt. This check never matches on a 502. The user sees a generic failure with no guidance to add a billing address.

**Contrast with course/event routes:** `POST /api/v1/courses/[id]/enroll` and `POST /api/v1/events/[id]/register` both call `resolveTabbyEligibility()` before forwarding to the handler and return a structured `400 {code: "TABBY_KSA_ONLY", reason: "...", error: "<localized message>"}` that the UI handles correctly.

## Root cause

The Tabby KSA eligibility gate was added to the course enroll and event register routes in [EXP-96](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-96/bug-restrict-tabby-checkout-to-ksa-traffic-only) (PR #439), but the subscription checkout route (`app/api/v1/commerce/subscriptions/checkout/route.ts`) was not updated. The schema (`SubscriptionCheckoutSchema`) uses `z.enum(PAYMENT_PROVIDERS)` which includes `"tabby"` as a valid value, so there is no schema-level guard either.

## Fix sketch

Apply the same eligibility check used in the enroll and register routes immediately after authentication and schema validation, before the command is dispatched:

```typescript
import {
  getCloudflareCountryCode,
  resolveTabbyEligibility,
  TABBY_KSA_ONLY_CODE,
  tabbyKsaOnlyMessage,
} from "@/lib/payments/payment-eligibility";

// Inside POST handler, after `const input = parsed.data;`:
if (input.provider === "tabby") {
  const cloudflareCountryCode = getCloudflareCountryCode(request.headers);
  const address = !cloudflareCountryCode
    ? await prisma.address.findUnique({
        where: {userId: session.user.id},
        select: {countryCode: true},
      })
    : null;
  const tabbyEligibility = resolveTabbyEligibility(request.headers, address?.countryCode);
  if (!tabbyEligibility.available) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      {
        error: tabbyKsaOnlyMessage(input.locale ?? "en"),
        code: TABBY_KSA_ONLY_CODE,
        reason: tabbyEligibility.reason,
      },
      {status: 400},
    );
  }
}
```

Also audit any other checkout routes (e.g., gift purchases, coupon-based checkout) that accept `provider` as an input to ensure consistent gating.

Related prior issues: [EXP-96](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-96/bug-restrict-tabby-checkout-to-ksa-traffic-only) (Tabby KSA restriction — added to enroll/register but not subscription checkout).
Verified by: workflow-orchestrator (primary), code-reviewer, qa-tester (parallel scan 2026-05-24).

