## Trigger scenario

Both `POST /api/v1/internal/storage-pending-reaper` and `POST /api/v1/internal/storage-orphan-reaper` (added in [EXP-81](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-81/bug-stale-pending-file-row-cleanup-r2-orphan-reaper), PR #456, merged 2026-05-24) authenticate the cron bearer token via plain string equality:

```typescript
if (!cronSecret || authHeader !== `Bearer ${cronSecret}`) {
  const {authorized, error: authError} = await requireAdmin();
  if (!authorized) {
    return NextResponse.json({error: ...}, {status: ...});
  }
}
```

**Scenario 1 — Missing CRON_SECRET (most urgent):** When `CRON_SECRET` is not set in the environment (misconfigured staging, fresh deploy before secrets are applied, or CI environment), `!cronSecret` evaluates to `true` and the bearer check is entirely skipped. Any authenticated admin session can then trigger:

* `reapStalePendingFiles()` — deletes all `File` rows with `status='pending'` older than the configured threshold, including files from uploads still in-flight if the threshold is mis-tuned.
* `reapR2Orphans()` — paginates `ListObjectsV2` across every R2 bucket tracked in the DB and issues `DeleteObjectCommand` for any object not in the DB snapshot. The 24h age gate protects against active in-flight uploads, but repeated on-demand invocation is expensive (full bucket scan) and destructive if triggered against a stale DB snapshot.

**Scenario 2 — Timing oracle attack:** When `CRON_SECRET` is set, `!==` branches on the first non-matching byte. An attacker with access to these endpoints can make high-frequency requests and reconstruct the secret byte-by-byte from response-time variance, enabling on-demand triggering of mass file deletion.

## Root cause

The `reservation-cleanup/route.ts` route added in the same [EXP-80](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-80/security-race-safe-storage-usage-ledger-userstorageusage-reservation) PR (#470, merged 2026-05-25) uses the correct pattern:

1. `crypto.timingSafeEqual` to prevent timing oracles.
2. Fail-closed (returns 500) when `CRON_SECRET` is unset rather than falling through to an admin-session fallback.

The [EXP-81](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-81/bug-stale-pending-file-row-cleanup-r2-orphan-reaper) routes predate this pattern and were not updated to match when [EXP-80](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-80/security-race-safe-storage-usage-ledger-userstorageusage-reservation) shipped.

## Suggested fix sketch

Apply the same guard used in `reservation-cleanup/route.ts` to both [EXP-81](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-81/bug-stale-pending-file-row-cleanup-r2-orphan-reaper) routes:

```typescript
const cronSecret = process.env.CRON_SECRET;
if (!cronSecret) {
  console.error("[storage-pending-reaper] CRON_SECRET not set — refusing all requests");
  return NextResponse.json({error: "Service misconfigured"}, {status: 500});
}
const authHeader = request.headers.get("authorization") ?? "";
const expected = `Bearer ${cronSecret}`;
const a = Buffer.from(authHeader);
const b = Buffer.from(expected);
const authorized = a.length === b.length && crypto.timingSafeEqual(a, b);
if (!authorized) return NextResponse.json({error: "Forbidden"}, {status: 403});
```

Remove the `requireAdmin()` fallback entirely. Admin-triggered reaper runs should go through a separate protected endpoint if needed.

## Related prior issues

* [EXP-81](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-81/bug-stale-pending-file-row-cleanup-r2-orphan-reaper) (Done) — parent issue where these routes were added (PR #456)
* [EXP-110](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-110/spinoff-exp-80-add-error-handling-to-reservation-cleanup-cron-route) (Backlog) — spinoff tracking error handling for `reservation-cleanup` cron (same family, different route)

