## Trigger Scenario

1. Deploy with `R2_ENDPOINT` and `R2_BUCKET_INVOICES` set, but `R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS` **omitted**.
2. `GET /api/v1/console/health` (as admin) returns `{"checks": {"storage": {"status": "ok"}}}` — no indication of misconfiguration.
3. `POST /api/v1/user/profile/cover` with any valid image → `uploadPublicAsset` throws `Error: R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS is not set` → HTTP 500. Same failure on every upload route invoking `uploadPublicAsset`: avatar, course thumbnail, event thumbnail, certification document, lesson video, community post thumbnail, attachment upload.

**Blast radius:** 100% of user-facing file upload requests fail silently (from the operator's perspective) while the health dashboard shows green.

## Root Cause

Commit `432dc30` (Fix R2 user upload bucket split, PR #505) moved all user content from `R2_BUCKET_STATIC` to `R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS` and added an explicit throw in `uploadPublicAsset` when the env var is absent:

```typescript
// apps/experts-app/src/lib/storage/commands/upload-public-asset.command.ts
const bucket = process.env.R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS;
if (!bucket) {
  throw new Error("R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS is not set");
}
```

`checkStorage` in the health route was not updated:

```typescript
// apps/experts-app/app/api/v1/console/health/route.ts
function checkStorage(): HealthCheck {
  if (!process.env.R2_ENDPOINT || !process.env.R2_BUCKET_INVOICES) {
    return degraded("R2 storage is not configured");
  }
  return ok();  // ← returns ok even when R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS is missing
}
```

Before the split, `R2_BUCKET_STATIC` fell back to `"static"` via `|| "static"` in `r2.ts` and never threw. The split removed that fallback and added a hard throw, but the health check was not updated to match the new critical env var.

## Suggested Fix

```typescript
function checkStorage(): HealthCheck {
  if (
    !process.env.R2_ENDPOINT ||
    !process.env.R2_BUCKET_INVOICES ||
    !process.env.R2_BUCKET_USER_UPLOADS
  ) {
    return degraded("R2 storage is not configured");
  }
  return ok();
}
```

Optionally also check `R2_BUCKET_CERTIFICATIONS` ([EXP-135](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-135/completeness-r2-bucket-certifications-consumed-in-upload-route-but)) while touching this function.

## Related prior issues

