## Severity

**Medium**

## Location

`apps/experts-app/app/api/v1/creator/events/[id]/route.ts:23`

## Description

The creator event detail GET route reads `isAdmin` from the JWT session claim rather than querying the database:

```typescript
// line 23 — JWT-derived, not DB-fresh
const isAdmin = Boolean(session.user.roles?.includes("admin"));

// line 24–33 — host check is only performed when !isAdmin
if (!isAdmin) {
  const isHost = event.hosts.some(h => h.userId === session.user.id);
  if (!isHost) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Forbidden" }, { status: 401 });
}
```

When `isAdmin` is `true` (from the JWT), the host ownership check is skipped entirely. If an admin's `isAdmin` flag has been cleared in the DB but their JWT has not yet expired, they can still fetch private event details for any event.

The `PUT` and `DELETE` handlers for `/api/v1/events/[id]` already use a DB-fresh lookup (the pattern established to fix [EXP-84](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-84/security-jwt-role-staleness-in-event-list-revoked-admin-bypasses-host)/89/90):

```typescript
// events/[id]/route.ts PUT/DELETE — correct pattern
const [event, dbUser] = await Promise.all([
  prisma.event.findUniqueOrThrow({ ... }),
  prisma.user.findUniqueOrThrow({ where: { id: session.user.id }, select: { isAdmin: true } }),
]);
const isAdmin = Boolean(dbUser.isAdmin);
```

The creator GET endpoint was not updated when the mutating endpoints were hardened.

## Attack Chain

**Attacker**: Admin whose DB `isAdmin` flag was cleared (account revoked/demoted), retaining a valid JWT with `roles: ["admin"]` for up to 30 days (JWT max-age from `auth.ts`).

**Controlled input**: The JWT session cookie containing stale `roles: ["admin"]`.

**Reachable path**: `GET /api/v1/creator/events/{eventId}` → line 23 reads `isAdmin = true` from JWT → skips host membership check → returns full event DTO including `meetingUrl`, `locationDetails.address`, `locationDetails.name`, and other private fields that are omitted from the public endpoint.

**Concrete impact**: Revoked admin can enumerate and read sensitive private event data (meeting URLs, private location credentials, draft events) across all events in the system for up to 30 days after their admin access is revoked.

## Recommended Remediation

Apply the same DB-fresh admin pattern used by the PUT/DELETE handlers:

```typescript
const [event, dbUser] = await Promise.all([
  prisma.event.findUnique({ where: { id }, include: { hosts: true } }),
  prisma.user.findUniqueOrThrow({ where: { id: session.user.id }, select: { isAdmin: true } }),
]);
const isAdmin = Boolean(dbUser.isAdmin);
```

## Related prior issues

[EXP-84](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-84/security-jwt-role-staleness-in-event-list-revoked-admin-bypasses-host) (resolved), [EXP-85](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-85/security-jwt-role-staleness-in-event-clone-revoked-admin-bypasses-host) (resolved), [EXP-89](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-89/security-jwt-role-staleness-in-delete-apiv1eventsid-revoked-admin) (resolved), [EXP-90](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-90/security-jwt-role-staleness-in-get-apiv1eventsid-revoked-admin-reads) (resolved), [EXP-91](https://linear.app/experts/issue/EXP-91/security-jwt-role-staleness-on-put-apiv1eventsid-revoked-admin) (resolved) — same class, previously fixed on mutating event routes. This GET endpoint was missed.

