## Summary

`handleCourseSubmit` guards only against `publishingStatus === "archived"`. It does not fetch or check `approvalStatus`, so an already-approved course can be re-submitted, which resets `approvalStatus` from `"approved"` to `"pending"` and forces a full re-review cycle — silently destroying the admin's prior approval.

## File

`apps/experts-app/src/lib/courses/catalog/handlers/course-submit.handler.ts` — `handleCourseSubmit`

## Root Cause

```ts
const current = await prisma.course.findUnique({
  where: {id: courseId},
  select: {id: true, publishingStatus: true},  // approvalStatus NOT fetched
});
if (current.publishingStatus === "archived") return {error: "...", status: 400};
// No guard for approvalStatus === "approved"
const updated = await prisma.course.update({
  where: {id: courseId},
  data: {publishingStatus: "submitted", approvalStatus: "pending"},  // ← silently resets
});
```

## Trigger Scenario

1. Admin approves a course (`approvalStatus: "approved"`, `publishingStatus: "approved"`).
2. Instructor calls `POST /api/v1/courses/{id}/submit`.
3. Handler checks only `publishingStatus !== "archived"` — passes.
4. Course is updated to `publishingStatus: "submitted"`, `approvalStatus: "pending"`.
5. Admin approval is silently destroyed; course must be re-reviewed.

## Fix

Add `approvalStatus` to the select and guard:

```ts
if (current.publishingStatus === "archived" || current.approvalStatus === "approved") {
  return {error: "Course is already approved", status: 409};
}
```

R3 fingerprint: `<!-- agent-fp: eaf8eedeb0b3 -->`.

## Summary

`handleCourseApprove` reads `approvalStatus` in its select clause but never validates it equals `"pending"` before approving. An admin can approve a course in `"rejected"` state without the instructor re-submitting, skipping the intended review cycle.

## File

`apps/experts-app/src/lib/courses/catalog/handlers/course-approve.handler.ts` — `handleCourseApprove`

## Root Cause

```ts
const current = await prisma.course.findUnique({
  where: {id: courseId},
  select: {id: true, publishingStatus: true, approvalStatus: true},
});
if (current.publishingStatus === "archived") return {error: "...", status: 400};
// No check: if (current.approvalStatus !== "pending") return {error: "...", status: 409};
const updated = await prisma.course.update({
  where: {id: courseId},
  data: {approvalStatus: "approved", publishingStatus: "approved"},
});
```

## Trigger Scenario

1. Admin rejects a course (`approvalStatus: "rejected"`).
2. Instructor does NOT re-submit.
3. Admin (accidentally or intentionally) calls `POST /api/v1/courses/{id}/approve`.
4. Course is approved directly from `"rejected"` state, bypassing the re-submission requirement.

## Fix

```ts
if (current.approvalStatus !== "pending") {
  return {error: "Course is not pending approval", status: 409};
}
```

